dataStructure.name: sid.org.tmforum.tip.resource.res.log.prot.EquipmentSwitchData
dataStructure.description:
This data type identifies the current protection switch status of an Equipment Protection Group.

This datatype is extendable
dataStructure.label: EquipmentSwitchData

child.name: equipmentSwitchReason
child.description:
This attribute contains the reason of the last switch.

This element is generated from an attribute.

This attribute is invariant

This attribute is optional
child.label: equipmentSwitchReason

child.name: epgRef
child.description:
This attribute identifies the Equipment Protection Group for which the protection switch status is being reported.

This element is generated from an attribute.

This attribute is invariant

This attribute is optional
child.label: epgRef

child.name: switchToEquipmentRef
child.description:
This attribute identifies the Equipment object that is working after the switch, or currently working if no protection switch is currently active.

This element is generated from an attribute.

This attribute is invariant

This attribute is optional
child.label: switchToEquipmentRef

child.name: equipmentProtectionType
child.description:
This attribute identifies the type of equipment protection for which the switch has occurred. The attribute can take on the following value: - "M_FOR_N", means that M pieces of equipment protect N pieces of equipment.

This element is generated from an attribute.

This attribute is invariant

This attribute is optional
child.label: equipmentProtectionType

child.name: protectedEquipmentRef
child.description:
This attribute identifies the name of the protected equipment. In case of an M:N equipment protection type, protectedEquipmentRef always identifies a worker Equipment object.

This element is generated from an attribute.

This attribute is invariant

This attribute is optional
child.label: protectedEquipmentRef

child.name: extensionInfo
child.description: a generic list of any type of elements. Used for vendor extensions or loose element encapsulation from other namespaces.
child.label: extensionInfo
